    "body": "> but it's not at all clear if this is the path on all platforms, or only on linux-like platforms. I'm on Windows.\n\nYes, that's the config path on Windows, too.\n\nThis issue can be reproduced with this code on Unix systems, too.\n```shell\n# Assuming ~/.foo/ does not exist\nSTARSHIP_CONFIG=~/.foo/bar.toml starship config foo bar\n```\n\nThis could probably be solved with a call to [`fs::create_dir_all`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/fs/fn.create_dir_all.html) to create the containing directory whenever trying to edit or write the file.",
